qas.question: The United Nations has been compared to what government in function and effectiveness?

answers.text: the pre-Constitutional United States Federal government

qas.question: In which aspects has the United Nations been compared to the pre-Constitutional United States Federal government?
The comparison of the United Nations to the pre-Constitutional United States Federal government gives us a comparison between what modern and historical legal topics of interest?

answers.text: modern treaty law and the historical Articles of Confederation

qas.question: Modern treaty law can be compared in function and effectiveness to the historical Articles of Confederation by comparing the pre-Constitutional United States Federal government with what modern institution?
What legal document formed the basis of the pre-Constitutional Federal government of the United States?
